        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down | Farnboro | Kent</placeName>
                    <date>Ap 26.</date>
                    <salute>Dear Mrs Thorley</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
<p>I must beg permission to express to you our deep obligation to your daughter &amp; our most earnest hope that her health may not be injured by her exertions I hope it will not appear presumptuous in me to say that her conduct struck me as throughout quite admirable. I never saw her once [yield] to her feelings as long as self restraint &amp; exertion were of any use— her judgment &amp; good sense never failed: her kindness, her devotion to our poor child could hardly have been excelled by that of a mother</p>
<p>Such conduct will, I trust hereafter be in some degree rewarded by the satisfaction your daughter must ever feel when she looks back at her exertions to save &amp; comfort our poor dear dying child. I earnestly hope that her health will be pretty soon established. My wife joins in kindest remembrance to yourself</p>
<p>Pray believe me &amp;c</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
    
        
